universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant BaldEagle : obj
constant Rabbit : obj
constant Squirrel : obj
constant Tiger : obj

constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Visits : obj → obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Likes : obj → obj → Prop
constant Needs : obj → obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Kind : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Green BaldEagle
axiom T2 : Visits BaldEagle Rabbit
axiom T3 : Round Rabbit
axiom T4 : Likes Rabbit BaldEagle
axiom T5 : ¬ Likes Rabbit Squirrel
axiom T6 : ¬ Needs Rabbit BaldEagle
axiom T7 : Round Squirrel
axiom T8 : Needs Squirrel Rabbit
axiom T9 : Needs Squirrel Tiger
axiom T10 : Visits Squirrel Rabbit
axiom T11 : Round Tiger
axiom T12 : Needs Tiger BaldEagle

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Likes x Rabbit ∧ Round x → Needs x BaldEagle
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Likes x Rabbit ∧ Needs x BaldEagle → Visits x Tiger
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x BaldEagle ∧ Green BaldEagle → Needs BaldEagle Squirrel
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x BaldEagle → Likes BaldEagle Rabbit
axiom R5 : Likes BaldEagle Tiger → Rough BaldEagle
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Rough x ∧ Needs x Rabbit → ¬ Likes x Rabbit
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x Rabbit → Visits Rabbit BaldEagle
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Squirrel → Round x
axiom R9 : ¬ Kind BaldEagle ∧ ¬ Likes BaldEagle Rabbit → Visits BaldEagle Squirrel

  sorry,

theorem bald_eagle_does_not_visit_tiger : ¬ Visits BaldEagle Tiger :=
begin
  intro H,
  have H1 : Likes BaldEagle Rabbit := R4 BaldEagle T2,
  have H2 : Rough BaldEagle := R5 H1,
  have H3 : Needs BaldEagle Rabbit := R1 BaldEagle (and.intro H1 T3),
  have H4 : ¬ Likes BaldEagle Rabbit := R6 BaldEagle (and.intro H2 H3),
  contradiction,
end

-- The answer is True
